23/12/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Democratic Party (DS) on Friday (December 21st) nominated current President Boris Tadic as its candidate in the forthcoming presidential elections on January 20th. 
About 19,000 DS members gave their support to Tadic -- 10,000 votes were necessary for the nomination.
Meanwhile, the Serbian Renewal Movement (SPO) announced on Saturday it will not nominate a candidate in the elections. 
SPO Deputy Chairman Srdjan Sreckovic said that the presidential vote will take place at a complicated time for Serbia, and the party's future steps will depend on the political situation and developments in the Kosovo situation. 
(Tanjug, RIA Novosti, PRIME-TASS, Beta, B92 - 21/12/07)
